'''''Star Wars: Tales from Mos Eisley''''' is a one-shot [[Star Wars comic books|comic]] that was published by [[Dark Horse Comics]] on [[March 26]], [[1996]]. It was written by [[Bruce Jones]] and illustrated by [[Bret Blevins]]. It contained the short comics [[Tales from Mos Eisley: Light Duty|''Light Duty'']], [[Tales from Mos Eisley: Mostly Automatic|''Mostly Automatic'']], and [[Tales from Mos Eisley: Heggs' Tale|''Heggs' Tale'']] (all of which had appeared in issues of the ''[[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine]]'') as well as a collection of one-page image pinups.

==Publisher's summary==
''"Mos Eisley Spaceport. You'll never find a more wretched hive of scum and villainy." With those words, Obi-Wan Kenobi introduced the most famous, not to mention dangerous, drinking establishment in the history of science fiction. Now, you can get a table of your own. Belly up to the bar and let the patrons regale you with a tale of Tatooine, a story of interstellar romance, and a saga of Rebel triumph. And please be sure to check your droids and your blaster at the door.''

